As far as we process your data in the case of a legal dispute for legal prosecution or legal defence, these data remain stored for the duration of the legal dispute or statutory limitation periods. The limitation period can be up to 30 years, whereby the regular limitation period ends after 3 years.
10. Transmission of your Data
We will only pass on your data to third parties if we are entitled to do so on the basis of your consent or if we are entitled or obliged to do so on the basis of the applicable law. The same applies if we receive your data from third parties, i.e. neither from you nor from companies commissioned by us.
An authorization exists both in the case in which third parties on our behalf collect data for us and transmit it to us, as well as in the case in which we on our part pass on data to other companies and these process the data on our behalf.
The latter is particularly the case if we do not carry out our business activities (e.g. IT services in connection with the operation of the website, creation and sending of newsletters) ourselves, but have them carried out by other companies, and this activity is connected with the processing of your data. In such cases, we have previously contractually obliged these companies to use the data only for the purposes permitted by law. We are authorised to control these companies in this respect.
There is a legal obligation, for example, to pass on data to criminal prosecution authorities.
11. Your rights (Objection, Revocation, Information, Correction, Blocking, Deletion, Transfer, Complaint)
11.1 Opposition
You can object to the processing of your personal data by us at any time for reasons arising from your particular situation. For this, you can use the contact possibilities mentioned in paragraph I. 1. If you file an objection, we will no longer process your personal data unless we can prove compelling reasons for the processing worthy of protection which outweighs your interests, rights and freedoms.
11.2 Revocation
Furthermore, you have the right to revoke any consent you have given with effect for the future. However, the legality of the data processing based on your consent remains unaffected until the revocation is exercised.
11.3 Other rights
You have the right at any time to receive information about your personal data stored by us free of charge, to correct incorrect data and to block or delete data. Furthermore, you have the right to receive your data in a structured, common and machine-readable format and to have your data transferred by us to someone else. Finally, you have the right to complain to a data protection authority.
With the exception of your right of complaint to the data protection authority, you can address your respective request to us by using the contact data mentioned in section I. 1.
12. Data Security
Your personal data will be transmitted encrypted over the internet. We secure our website and other systems by technical and organizational measures, in particular the encryption technology TSL (Transport Layer Security), against loss, destruction, access, alteration or distribution of your data by unauthorized persons.
All data collected and processed in connection with our website is stored on servers located in Frankfurt/a.M. and therefore subject to the high standards of the General Data Protection Regulation.
We take the appropriate technical and organisational measures within Art. 32 DS-GVO, taking into account the state of the art, the implementation costs and the type, scope, circumstances and purposes of the processing as well as the probability and severity of the infringement of rights and freedoms of natural persons.
In this sense, the following measures, among others, are taken to protect your data and to secure it against loss, destruction, access, alteration and distribution by unauthorised persons:
Ensuring the confidentiality, integrity, availability and resilience of the systems and services in connection with the processing;
Ensure rapid recovery of the availability of personal data in the event of a physical or technical incident;
Implement procedures to regularly review, evaluate and evaluate the effectiveness of the technical and organisational measures taken to ensure the security of the processing.
Please be aware that while we strive to provide a secure and reliable website for our users, the absolute confidentiality of any communications or materials transmitted in the course of using our website cannot be guaranteed.
